an class="Wrd"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">18</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">-</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">8</span></span> <span class="EmphasizedTxt">Stainless</span> <span class="Wrd"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Steel</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">â€”</span></span>Has excellent corrosion <span class="Wrd">resistance.</span> May be mildly <span class="Wrd">magnetic.</span> </p><p class="PrsnttnCpy smallVerticalGutter"><span class="Wrd"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Titanium</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">â€”</span></span>Resists corrosion from salt water and stands up to more chemicals than stainless <span class="Wrd">steel.</span> Itâ€™s <span class="Wrd">strong,</span> yet <span class="Wrd">40%</span> lighter than <span class="Wrd">steel.</span> </p><p class="PrsnttnCpy smallVerticalGutter"><span class="Wrd"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Brass</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">â€”</span></span>Nonmagnetic with very good corrosion <span class="Wrd">resistance.</span> An excellent conductor of <span class="Wrd">electricity,</span> itâ€™s usually softer than steel and stainless <span class="Wrd">steel.</span> </p><p class="PrsnttnCpy smallVerticalGutter"><span class="Wrd"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Aluminum</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">â€”</span></span>Offers mild resistance to <span class="Wrd">corrosion.</span> Itâ€™s nonmagnetic and one-third the weight of <span class="Wrd">steel.</span> </p><p class="PrsnttnCpy smallVerticalGutter"><span class="Wrd"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Steel</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">â€”</span></span>This low-strength general purpose metal is often plated with zinc for corrosion <span class="Wrd">resistance.</span> </p><p class="PrsnttnCpy"><span class="Wrd"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Plastic</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">â€”</span></span>Plastic screws come in economical <span class="Wrd">nylon;</span> impact-resistant <span class="Wrd">polycarbonate;</span> chemical-resistant <span class="Wrd">PTFE;</span> and high-strength <span class="Wrd">PEEK.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="clearDiv"></div></div><div class="largeVerticalGutter"><div class="floated GridCell SubPrsnttnCell" colspan="1" style="width:791px;"><div class="PrsnttnStructure5 SubPrsnttn" id="Sub_1223016.1"><div><div class="FullGenInfo_Subhead smallVerticalGutter"><span>Finishes</span></div><div><div class="CpyCntnr" style="width:700px;"><p class="PrsnttnCpy smallVerticalGutter"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Black</span> <span class="Wrd"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Oxide</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">â€”</span></span>Provides a decorative <span class="Wrd">finish,</span> adds mild corrosion resistance in dry <span class="Wrd">environments,</span> and makes screws easier to <span class="Wrd">thread.</span> </p><p class="PrsnttnCpy smallVerticalGutter"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Zinc</span> <span class="Wrd"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Plated</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">â€”</span></span>Enhances corrosion resistance in wet <span class="Wrd">environments.</span> </p><p class="PrsnttnCpy smallVerticalGutter"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Chrome</span> <span class="Wrd"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Plated</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">â€”</span></span>Bright and <span class="Wrd">attractive.</span> Offers good corrosion <span class="Wrd">resistance.</span> </p><p class="PrsnttnCpy smallVerticalGutter"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Cadmium</span> <span class="Wrd"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Plated</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">â€”</span></span>Adds superior corrosion resistance and makes screws easier to <span class="Wrd">thread.</span> </p><p class="PrsnttnCpy smallVerticalGutter"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Black</span> <span class="EmphasizedTxt">Ultra</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">-</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Corrosion</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">-</span><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Resistant</span> <span class="Wrd"><span class="EmphasizedTxt">Coated</span